<td width=50% border=0 valign="top">(Thursday 21 April 2011) Almost nine out of ten British women are not keen on achieving the dream of Kate Middleton, future wife of Prince William, according to a survey carried out by the internet marketing research company YouGov.  The principal reason is the fact that Kate will no longer be able to carry out a normal life after her marriage to William this coming 29 April.  Everything concerning Kate including her movements, dress fashion and anything said by her will make media news.  It is certain that her life will be full of pressures.
